SIMPLE: collimator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Collimator
<hw>Col"li*ma`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A telescope arranged and used to determine
errors of collimation, both vertical and horizontal.</def>
<rj><au>Nichol.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Optics)</fld> <def>A tube having a convex lens at
one end and at the other a small opening or slit which is at the
principal focus of the lens, used for producing a beam of parallel rays;
also, a lens so used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Collin</ent>⟦br⟧
